        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 4:14PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Grover Hot Springs, or 8 miles east of Carson Pass, moving north at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Woodfords, Grover Hot Springs, Mesa Vista, Alpine Village, Hope
Valley, Junction CA 88 W And CA 89 N (picketts Junction), Indian
Creek Campground, Markleeville, Turtle Rock Campground, Paynesville,
Indian Creek Reservoir, Alpine County Airport, and Luther Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
